# Current Codebase Violations Summary

This document identifies violations of the naming conventions found in the codebase.

## Component Export Violations

### Issue: Default Exports
**38 components** currently use `export default` instead of named exports.

**Affected Files:**
- `components/app-header.tsx` - Has both named and default export
- `components/base-panel/base-panel.tsx` - Has both named and default export
- All components in `components/landing-page/` (12 files)
- All components in `components/tools-feature/` (9 files)
- All components in `components/upload-feature/` (6 files)
- All components in `components/creator-badge/` (5 files)
- All components in `components/dropdown-controls/` (5 files)
- All components in `components/result-image-preview/` (3 files)

**Fix Required:**
1. Remove `export default` statements
2. Keep only named exports: `export const ComponentName`
3. Update all import statements to use named imports
4. Update index.ts files to export named exports only

**Example Fix:**
```typescript
// Before
export const AppHeader: React.FC = () => { ... };
export default AppHeader;

// After
export const AppHeader: React.FC = () => { ... };
```

